Whenever I have an appointment at UI Health and then time to spend at the library across the street from Subway, then I will always go to this Subway (which is now my favorite one in the city of Chicago). It is located in the lovely neighborhood of Little Italy among several other older Italian restaurants and some new and upcoming vegetarian and burger hot spots. The customer service is fabulous as well as the atmosphere. It is very clean, has a lot of floor space and is not cramped like many Subways are in the city, and has a very soothing ambience even though the music that is played is very upbeat. It draws a motley mix of clientele: high school and college students, business professionals, retirees, etc. The food ingredients are top-knotch, and when they make the sandwiches, they are so massive and delicious. Everyone who works there, as well as the management are extremely pleasant and personable. I highly recommend this Subway!
